Because of piracy P2P applications have already become a threat to big companies a long time ago.

And yet, those companies have not been able to implement anything technical to completely stop it.
Hence, they resort to things like try blocking the DNS of the people hosting the torrents/magnetic links, sending threatening DMCA letters to users or adding DRM software like Denuvo to their products.

Because of the Tor integration, it seems ZeroNet solves both of the first problems.
And even if the ISP tries blocking any access to the known Tor relays it still possible to bypass it with bridges and whatnot.
